2,000 modern rifles for Indian Army|date=February 12, 2019|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-07-09}}</ref> Deliveries started in December 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/indian-army-gets-new-american-assault-rifles-in-kashmir-valley-against-terrorists-pakistan-army-on-loc/articleshow/72467643.cms|title=Indian Army gets new American assault rifles in Kashmir Valley against terrorists, Pakistan Army on LoC|date=December 11, 2019|website=[[Asian News International]]|via=[[The Economic Times]]|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[CAR 816|Caracal International CAR 816]]\n|[[File:CAR 816.jpg|CAR 816|150px]]\n|[[Carbine]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{UAE}}\n|'''Status: On Order.'''\nOrder placed for 94,000 units of CAR 816 carbine.\n|-\n|[[Heckler & Koch HK416]]\n|[[File:HK416.jpg|frameless|206x206px]]\n|[[Carbine]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{GER}}\n|'''Status: In Service.'''\nUsed by Special forces\n|-\n|[[T91 assault rifle]]\n|[[File:T91 assault rifle.jpg|150px]]\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{TWN}}\n|'''Status: In Service.''' 1000+ unit of this rifle were brought\n|-\n|[[M16 rifle]]\n|[[File:M16a1m16a2m4m16a45wi.jpg|frameless|146x146px]]\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{USA}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces\n|-\n|[[M4 carbine|M4A1 Carbine]]\n|[[File:PEO M4 Carbine RAS M68 CCO.jpg|M4A1 Assault Rifle|150px]]||[[Assault rifle]]||[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]||{{USA}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces, including PARA SF and Ghatak SF and MARCOS.\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Sniper rifles\n|-\n|[[Steyr SSG 69]]\n|[[File:Steyr SSG 69.jpg|Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]|| 7.62\u00d751mm NATO ||{{AUT}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard bolt-action sniper rifle.\n|-\n|[[Mauser|Mauser SP66]]\n|[[File:Mauser sp66.JPG|Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]|| 7.62\u00d751mm NATO ||{{GER}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard bolt-action sniper rifle.\n|-\n|[[SIG Sauer SSG 3000]]\n|[[File:SIG Sauer SSG 3000.jpg|Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]|| 7.62\u00d751mm NATO ||{{GER}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard bolt-action sniper rifle.\n|-\n|[[Dragunov Sniper Rifle|Dragunov SVD]]\n|[[File:SVD Dragunov.jpg|Dargunov Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]||[[7.62\u00d754mmR]]||{{USSR}}<br>{{IND}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard Designated Marksman rifle(DMR). To be replaced by a 7.62mm NATO DMR under the Army modernisation plan.<ref name=\"ndtv.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/india-news/re-arming-the-indian-armys-troops-with-lethal-modern-weapons-505844|title=Re-arming the Indian Army's troops with lethal, modern weapons|author=Nitin Gokhale|date=28 November 2012|work=NDTV.com|accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Barrett M95]]\n|[[File:Barrett M95SP.jpg|150px]]\n|[[Sniper rifle]]\n|.50 BMG\n|{{USA}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Small numbers. Used in anti-sniping role.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/army-goes-for-urgent-buy-of-sniper-rifles/articleshow/67496103.cms|title=Army goes for urgent buy of sniper rifles {{!}} India News - Times of India|date=12 January 2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Heckler & Koch PSG1]]\n|[[File:PSG1 and MSG 90.jpg|Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]|| 7.62\u00d751mm NATO ||{{GER}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard semi-automatic sniper rifle\nused by Indian Army, NSG, MARCOS.\n|-\n|Beretta Scorpio TGT\n|\n|[[Sniper rifle]]\n|[[.338 Lapua Magnum]]\n|{{ITA}}\n|'''Status: In service.'''<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n|[[Sako TRG M10]]\n|[[File:Interpolitex 2012 (482-30).jpg|150px]]\n|[[Sniper rifle]]\n|[[.338 Lapua Magnum]]\n|{{FIN}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Small numbers, used by Para SF.<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n|[[Barrett Model 98B]]\n|[[File:Barrett M98B.jpg|150px]]\n|[[Sniper rifle]]\n|[[.338 Lapua Magnum]]\n|{{USA}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Used by Special Forces including NSG.\n|-\n|[[IMI Galil#7.62mm variants|IMI Galil 7.62 Sniper]]\n|[[File:Galil-Sniper-Galatz-r001.jpg|Galil Sniper|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle|Sniper Rifle]]|| 7.62\u00d751mm NATO ||{{ISR}}||'''Status: In service.''' For use by Indian Army Special Forces snipers.\n|-\n|[[Denel NTW-20]]\n|[[File:NTW-20 rifle.jpg|frameless|150px]]\n\n|[[Anti-materiel rifle|Anti-material rifle]]|| 14.5\u00d7114mm, 20\u00d782mm and 20\u00d7110mm Hispano-Suiza ||{{ZAF}}||'''Status: In service.''' Bought in small numbers.\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Machine Guns\n|-\n|[[IMI Negev]]\n|[[File:IWI-Negev-Zachi-Evenor-01-white.jpg|IMI Negev|150px]]||[[Light machine gun]]||5.56\u00d745mm NATO||{{ISR}}||'''Status: In service. 16,479 Negev LMG are on order and will replace INSAS LMG''' \n|-\n|[[M249]]\n|[[File:M249 Automatic Rifle.jpg|[[M249]]|150px]]||[[Light Machine Gun]]|| 5.56x45mm NATO ||{{BEL}}<br>{{USA}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by the NSG.\n|-\n|[[Uk vz. 59]]\n|[[File:UK vz.59.jpg|150px]]\n|[[General-purpose machine gun]]\n|[[7.62\u00d754mmR]]\n|{{CZS}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Small numbers, used by Para SF and SFF.\n|-\n|[[MAG 58|MG 2A1]]<hr>[[MAG 58|MG 5A]]<hr>[[MAG 58|MG 6A]]\n|[[File:FN MAG.jpg|FN MAG|MG 2A1|150px]]||[[General purpose machine gun]]|| 7.62\u00d751mm NATO ||{{BEL}}<br>{{IND}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard section-Medium Machine Gun for infantry battalions, Indian-made MAG 58 version. Also in service as the MG 5A (Co-axial) and MG 6A (Commander's gun) with some armoured vehicles.\n|-\n|[[M2 Browning]]\n|[[File:M2 Browning, Mus\u00e9e de l'Arm\u00e9e.jpg|M2 Browning HMG|150px]]||[[Heavy machine gun]]||[[.50 BMG]]||{{USA}}||'''Status: In service.''' M2HB variant in service, used in small numbers.<ref name=\"jones2009\">Jones, Richard D. ''Jane's Infantry Weapons 2009/2010''. Jane's Information Group; 35 edition (27 January 2009). {{ISBN|978-0-7106-2869-5}}.</ref>\n|-\n|[[PK machine gun|PKM]]\n|[[File:7,62 KK PKM Helsinki 2012.JPG|PKM Machine Gun|150px]]||