ike Vehicles to Indian Army|date=10 May 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Tata LPTA 713 TC\n|[[File:2.5 ton (2).jpg|frameless|220x220px]]|| Medium 4X4 truck ||  ||{{IND}}|| 2.5 Ton truck. Manufactured by [[Vehicle Factory Jabalpur]].\n|-\n| [[Ashok Leyland Stallion|Ashok Leyland Stallion Mk III/Mk IV]] \n|[[File:Stallion Indian Army.jpg|200x200px]]|| Medium 4x4<br>6x6 Truck || 60,000 || {{IND}} || 5 Ton trucks, in a wide range of configurations manufactured by [[Vehicle Factory Jabalpur]].\n\n|-\n| [[Tata Motors|Tata]] LPTA 2038 HMV \n||| 6x6 High Mobility Truck || || {{IND}} || 1858 units on order.<ref>http://www.tatamotors.com/press/tata-motors-bags-additional-order-for-619-nos-of-6-x-6-high-mobility-vehicles-from-indian-army/</ref> To augment and replace older BEML Tatra 6x6 fleet.\n|-\n| [[Bharat Earth Movers Limited|BEML]] Tatra \n|[[File:Know Your Army Jalandhar 2009-83.jpg|200x200px]]|| Heavy 4x4 trucks<br>6x6 trucks<br>8x8 trucks<br>10x10 trucks<br>12x12 trucks || 7000<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.ibnlive.com/news/no-complaints-against-tatra-trucks-defence-ministry/242913-3.html |title=No complaints against Tatra trucks: Defence Ministry |publisher=M.ibnlive.com |date= |accessdate=2012-04-21}}</ref>|| {{IND}}<br>{{CZS}} || License produced [[Tatra (company)|Tatra]] Force heavy truck. Various models. Used for carrying sensitive equipment like Radars as well as vehicle for Pinaka and Smerch MBRL systems.\n|-\n| Ashok Leyland Super Stallion \n|[[File:Ashok Leyland Stallion 6X6 (9686037415).jpg|200x200px]]|| 6x6, 8x8, 10x10 Truck ||  || {{IND}} ||<ref name=\"super_stallion\">http://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/companies/new-defence-orders-to-be-executed-over-2-years-ashok-leyland-1026357.html</ref> 10,12 and 15 Ton trucks.\n|-\n| Ashok Leland Super Stallion FAT\n|[[File:Le1s 20180228-142634-1-1.jpg|frameless|220x220px]]\n| Artillery Tractor 6x6 || 450 || {{IND}} ||<ref name=\"super_stallion\"/>\n|-\n|Volvo FH 12\n|[[File:Agni-V missile during rehearsal of Republic Day Pa