ayanta chassis and manufactured by [[Heavy Vehicles Factory]].\n|-\n| [[MT-55|Bridge Laying MT-55]] \n|[[File:MT-55 Armoured Bridge layer - geograph.org.uk - 1806494.jpg|200x200px]]||[[Armoured vehicle-launched bridge]] || || {{USSR}}{{IND}}\n| Based on T-55 Tank\n|-\n| [[T-72|T-72 BLT]] \n|[[File:Bridge Layer Tank on Ajeya manufactured by Heavy Vehicles Factory (HVF) of Ordnance Factory Board.jpg|none|thumb|220x220px]]||[[Armoured vehicle-launched bridge]] || 18 ||{{IND}} || Developed by [[CVRDE]] and manufactured by [[Heavy Vehicles Factory]].\n|-\n| [[DRDO Sarvatra|Sarvatra]] \n|[[File:15 Metre Sarvatra Bridging System passes through the Rajpath during the full dress rehearsal for the Republic Day Parade-2013, in New Delhi on January 23, 2013.jpg|none|thumb]]|| truck-mounted, multi-span, mobile bridging system || || {{Flagu|India}} || 8x8 truck-mounted bridging system<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Army/Galleries/Mod/Logistics/Engineers/0475.jpg.html |title=Sarvatra Bridging System [www.bharat-rakshak.com&#93; |publisher=Bharat-rakshak.com |accessdate=2013-08-23 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121104072158/http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Army/Galleries/Mod/Logistics/Engineers/0475.jpg.html |archivedate=4 November 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/MONITOR/4-5/kapoor.html |title=BHARAT RAKSHAK MONITOR - Volume 4(5) |publisher=Bharat-rakshak.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-23 |df=dmy }}{{dead link|date=January 2018|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Pontoon bridge|Floating bridge]]\n|[[File:The Amphibious floating bridge & Ferry System gliding down the Rajpath during the Republic Day Parade - 2006, in New Delhi on January 26, 2006.jpg|none|thumb|220x220px]]\n|[[Armoured vehicle-launched bridge]]\n|\n|{{Flagu|India}}\n|This 42 tonne mammoth is the Amphibious Floating Bridge and Ferry System (AFFS) developed by DRDO, for the ferry of traffic across large and deep water obstacles. The 10m x 3.6m x 4m vehicle can covert to a fully decked bridge configuration of length 28.4 metres, in 9 minutes. The vehicle has a maximum speed of 55 km/h on road, 40 km/h cross country and an aquatic mobility of 2.7 m/sec with twin pump jets.\n|-\n| [[Vijayanta|CEASE]] \n||| [[Main battle tank]] || 6 || {{IND}} || The Canal Embankment Assault Equipment\n|-\n| [[Armoured Engineer Reconnaissance Vehicle|AERV]] \n|[[File:The AERV passing through the Rajpath during the full dress rehearsal for Republic Day Parade - 2005, in New Delhi on January 23, 2005.jpg|none|thumb]]|| Military Engineering Vehicle ||16\n|{{IND}} || BMP-2 based engineering and reconnaissance vehicle (Armoured Engineer Reconnaissance Vehicle) being manufactured at [[Ordnance Factory Medak]].\n|-\n|[[BMP-2]]\n|[[File:Yudh Abhyas-09 BMP.JPG|200x200px]]||Armoured Amphibious Bulldozer || || {{IND}} || BMP-2 with turret removed and bulldozer blade and other engineering equipment added and being manufactured at [[Ordnance Factory Medak]].\n|-\n| [[FV180 Combat Engineer Tractor]] \n|[[File:FV180 Comabat Engineer Tractor (CET) pic2.JPG|200x200px]]||Armoured combat engineering vehicle || 39 || {{GBR}} ||\n|-\n| VFJ Light Recovery Vehicle \n||| Light Recovery Vehicle (4x4) || || {{IND}} || Manufactured at [[Vehicle Factory Jabalpur]].\n|-\n| [[Ordnance Factory Board Mine Protected Vehicle|Yuktirath Light Recovery Vehicle]] \n||| Armoured Light Recovery Vehicle (4x4) || || {{Flagu|India}} || Manufactured at [[Ordnance Factory Medak]].\n|-\n| Mat Ground Surfacing CL-70 \n||| All Terrain vehicle|| || {{IND}} || Mounted on Tatra vehicle with automated laying and recovery has been developed for providing mobility in sandy and marshy terrain.<ref>[http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Equipment/Engineering/378-Mat-Fording.html Mat-Fording] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121219012740/http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Equipment/Engineering/378-Mat-Fording.h