mes.com/india/Defence-ministry-scraps-Rs-6000cr-tender-for-purchase-of-197-helicopters/articleshow/41192969.cms |title=Defence ministry scraps Rs 6000cr tender for purchase of 197 helicopters |publisher=The Times of India |date=29 August 2014 |accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[File:Arjun Mk II side (2).JPG|frameless]]\n|118(Mk2)\n|-\n| [[T-90|T-90S \"Bhishma\"]]<hr> [[T-90|T-90M]] ||[[File:Indian Army T-90.jpg|200x200px]]\n|[[Main battle tank|Main Battle Tank]]|| 1,640<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/catherine-cameras-an-integral-part-of-armys-t90-main-battle-tanks/article9262621.ece|title=Catherine cameras an integral part of Army\u2019s T-90 main battle tanks|last=Nair-Ghaswalla|first=Amrita|date=2016-10-24|newspaper=The Hindu Business Line|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref> \n| {{RUS}}<br>{{IND}} \n| '''In service.''' Initial contract for 310 \"T-90S\" signed in 2001. Another contract signed on 26 October 2006 for 330 T-90M MBTs. A third contract was signed in December 2007 for 347 upgraded T-90Ms. In all, India plans to have over 1500 T-90 tanks in service by 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.strategypage.com/htmw/htarm/articles/20081004.aspx |title=Armor: The Frugal T-90 |publisher=Strategypage.com |date=4 October 2008 |accessdate=2010-02-07}}</ref> A contract for additional 464 T-90S was placed in November 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/rs-20000-crore-worth-orders-placed-to-get-464-t90s/articleshow/71963553.cms|title=464 Bhishma tanks to made in Tamil Nadu\u2019s Avadi|date=2019-11-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.janes.com/article/92481/indian-mod-awards-ofb-usd2-8-billion-contract-to-licence-build-464-additional-t-90s-mbts|title=Indian MoD awards OFB USD2.8 billion contract to licence-build 464 additional T-90S MBTs|date=2019-11-11}}</ref>\n\n<!-- full text = Initially contract for 310 \"T-90S\" signed in 2001. A contract, worth $800 million, was signed on 26 October 2006, for another 330 T-90M MBTs that were to be built with locally sourced raw materials. A third contract, worth $1.23 billion, was signed in December 2007 for 347 upgraded T-90Ms, the bulk of which will be licence-assembled built by [[Heavy Vehicles Factory]]. The Indian Army would begin receiving its first T-90M main battle tank (MBT) in completely knocked-down condition from Russia's Nizhny Tagil-based Uralvagonzavod JSC by the end of 2009.<ref name=\"globalsecurity.org\">{{cite web|author=John Pike |url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/india/t-90.htm |title=T-90 Bhisma |publisher=Globalsecurity.org |date= |accessdate=2010-02-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=RIA Novosti Dmitry Korobeinikov |url=http://www.en.beta.rian.ru/mlitary_news/20090824/155910756.html |title=Indian army receives first T-90 tanks made under Russian license | Top Russian news and analysis online | 'RIA Novosti' newswire |publisher=En.beta.rian.ru |date=24 August 2009 |accessdate=2010-02-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090904203207/http://en.beta.rian.ru/mlitary_news/20090824/155910756.html |archivedate=4 September 2009 |df=dmy }}</ref> In all, India plans to have 310 T-90S and 1,330 T-90M tanks in service by 2020 (total of 1,657 tanks with upgradation of night visions by 2020).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.strategypage.com/htmw/htarm/articles/20081004.aspx |title=Armor: The Frugal T-90 |publisher=Strategypage.com |date=4 October 2008 |accessdate=2010-02-07}}</ref> Manufactured locally in India. Rs10,000-crore purchase of 354 new T-90MS tanks for six tank regiments for the China border has been approved.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/india/news/army-scuttles-arjun-trials-to-push-through-russian-t-90-purchase/493676/ |title=Army scuttles Arjun trials to push through Russian T-90 purchase |publisher=Business Standard |date=26 November 2012 |accessdate=2012-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.armyrecognition.com/september_2013_defense_industry_military_news_uk/india_has_approved_the_manufacture_of_235_t-90_main_battle_tanks_under_russian_license_1909131.html |title=India has approved the manufacture of 235 T-90 main battle tanks under Russian license. Further 464 T90 SM to be manufactured |date=19 September 2013}}</ref> This takes total no. of T-90 tanks to 2011.  In an effort to improve night-fighting capacity, 1400 [[night vision]] devices for drivers are to be procured.  They are based on uncooled [[thermography|thermal imaging]] technology developed by [[Defence Research and Development Organisation|DRDO]].<ref name=Sputnik20161206>{{cite web|url=https://sputniknews.com/asia/201612051048193626-indian-army-t-90/|title=Indian Army to Equip T-90 Tanks for Night Fighting|publisher=Sputnik International|date=5 Dec 2016|accessdate=6 Dec 2016}}</ref>-->\n|-\n| [[T-72 operators and variants#India|T-72 Ajeya]]<hr>[[T-72 operators and variants#India|Combat Improved Ajeya]] \n|| [[File:T-72 Ajeya1.jpg|200x200px]]\n|[[Main battle tank|Main Battle Tank]]|| 2410<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.defencenews.in/defence-news-internal.asp?get=new&id=1466 |title=Defence News - Army Opts For T-90s Battle Tanks |publisher=Defencenews.in |accessdate=2013-08-23 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130724041113/http://defencenews.in/defence-news-internal.asp?get=new&id=1466 |archivedate=24 July 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Equipment/Armour/337-T-72m1-MBT.html \n|title=T-72M1 Main Battle Tank |publisher=Bharat Rakshak |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090606093155/http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Equipment/Armour/337-T-72m1-MBT.html |archivedate=6 June 2009 |accessdate=14 June 2012}}</ref> || {{USSR}}<br>{{POL}}<br>{{IND}} || '''In service.''' 968 T72M1 have been upgraded by [[Heavy Vehicles Factory]], while requests for proposal for upgrading approximately 1,000 other T-72's have been sent to various firms in Israel, Russia, Poland and France.{{Citation needed|date=December 2009}}. Ajeya-M2 Standard equivalent to the Polish [[PT-91 Twardy]]. Manufactured locally in India. Will be replaced by Future Ready Combat Vehicle.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.janes.com/article/75533/Indian-army-fresh-RIF-for-future-ready-combat-vehicle|title=Indian Army issues fresh RFI for Future Ready Combat Vehicle |work=Jane's 360|access-date=2017-11-08}}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" | [[Infantry fighting vehicle]]s\n|-\n| [[BMP-2#India|BMP-2 \"Sarath\"]] || [[File:Indian Army BMP-2.jpg|200x200px]]\n|[[Infantry fighting vehicle]]|| 2691<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/shortfall-of-bmp-infantry-fighting-vehicles-affecting-operational-preparedness-of-army-cag/|title=Shortfall of BMP infantry fighting vehicles affecting operational preparedness of Army: CAG|date=2015-12-19|newspaper=The Indian Express|access-date=2016-10-28}}</ref> || {{USSR}}<br>{{Flagu|India}} || '''In service.''' Being modernised with TISAS (Thermal Imaging Stand Alone Sights), better fire control, and more modern ATGM armament (Konkurs M). BMP-1 has been phased out and the upgraded BMP-2 is BMP-2M with two thermobaric missiles and two tandem warhead Konkurs missiles. It also has an integrated TI sight, an LRF, and has an AGL mounted on the turret which is also stabilised in the horizontal plane. 100 added each year. To enhance the rate to 125 a year.<ref name=\"Indian Army: Armoured Fighting Vehicles\"/> Currently ~2500 are in active service.<ref name=\"Indian Army: Armoured Fighting Vehicles\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Equipment/Armour/346-BMP-2.html |title=Land Forces Site \u2013 BMP-2 |publisher=Bharat Rakshak |date=20 February 2002 |accessdate=2012-04-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121007005545/http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Equipment/Armour/346-BMP-2.html |archivedate=7 October 2012 |df=dmy }}</ref> Manufactured locally in India by [[Ordnance Factory Medak]].  All BMP-2/2K vehicles are to be upgraded to BMP-2M standard.<ref>[http://www.deagel.com/news/Indian-Army-to-Upgrade-its-BMP-22K-Infantry-Combat-Vehicles-to-BMP-2M-Standard_n000011456.aspx Indian Army to Upgrade its BMP-2/2K Infantry Combat Vehicles to BMP-2M Standard] - Deagel.com, 6 May 2013</ref>\n|-\n|'''[[Abhay IFV]]'''\n|\n|[[Infantry fighting vehicle]]\n|\n|{{Flagu|India}}\n|Status:approx 2600 planned to replace the old bmp-2\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"align: center;\" | [[Armoured Personnel Carrier]]s\n|-\n| [[BTR-50]] || [[File:BTR-50-latrun-1-2.jpg|200x200px]] \n|[[Armoured Personnel Carrier]]||100+ || {{USSR}} || Status: Total 200 in service.\n|-\n| [[TATA Kestrel]] ||\n|[[Armoured personnel carrier]]\n|\n|{{Flag|India}}\n|Under development. Expected to be ready by 2017-18. Around 1000+ planned<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiandefensenews.in/2016/03/production-of-infantry-combat-vehicle.html|title=PRODUCTION OF INFANTRY COMBAT VEHICLE WILL START SIX YEARS FROM NOW: TATA MOTORS|last=|first=|date=2016-03-09|website=Indiandenfensenews|publisher=INDIANDEFENSE NEWS|access-date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"align: center;\" | [[Tank destroyer]]s\n|-\n| [[Nag (missile)#Namica|NAMICA]] || [[File:Nag with NAMICA Defexpo-2008.JPG|200x200px]]\n|[[Tank destroyer|Tank Destroyer]]|| 0 || {{Flag|India}} || Ordered. BMP-2 based Nag missile carrier. Advanced version on order after successful trial in July 2012. 13 units ordered with option for further orders of 200. Production started jointly by [[Ordnance Factory Medak]] and L&T.\n|-\n|[[BRDM-2|9P148]]\n|[[File:BRDM-2 Anti-tank vehicle.jpg|200x200px]]\n|[[Tank destroyer]]\n|\n|{{USSR}}\n|Used as a Tank destroyer.\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"align: center;\" | [[Reconnaissance vehicle]]s\n|-\n| [[Carrier Mortar Tracked|CMT]] ||[[File:The Carrier Mortar Tracked Vehicle gliding down the Rajpath during the Republic Day Parade - 2006, in New