118_light_gun#Other_variants|Light Field Gun]] || [[File:Ranjit_Lal_Jetley_at_the_Pragati_Maidan_Defence_exhibition.jpg|200x200px]]\n| [[Field gun]] || 700+ || {{IND}} || '''In service.''' 105mm gun. Ongoing upgrade.\n|-\n| [[FV433 Abbot SPG]] \n|[[File:Abbot self propelled gun.jpg|200x200px]]|| [[Self-propelled artillery]] || ~80 || {{GBR}} || '''In service/Being replaced.''' 105&nbsp;mm [[howitzer]]. Being replaced by the K9 VAJRA-T.\n|-\n| [[2S1 Gvozdika]] \n|[[File:Ukrainian 2S1 Gvozdika SPG.jpg|200x200px]]|| [[Self-propelled artillery]] || 110 || {{USSR}} || '''In service/Being replaced.'''122&nbsp;mm [[howitzer]]. Being replaced by the K9 VAJRA-T.\n|-\n|[[K9 Thunder]]\n|[[File:Rajnath Singh in the K9 VAJRA-T on January 16, 2020.jpg|200x200px]]||[[Self-propelled artillery]]||50||{{ROK}}<BR>{{IND}}||'''In service.'''155&nbsp;mm [[howitzer]], 100 units ordered with an option for an additional 50, variant of [[K9 Thunder]]. Will be manufactured by [[Larsen & Toubro]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.defenceupdate.in/mod-concludes-deal-lt-k9-vajra-t-howitzers/|title=MoD concludes deal with L&T for K9 Vajra-T Howitzers \u2014 Defence Update {{!}} Defence Update|website=www.defenceupdate.in|access-date=2016-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161028020452/http://www.defenceupdate.in/mod-concludes-deal-lt-k9-vajra-t-howitzers/|archive-date=28 October 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.janes.com/article/69168/india-s-acquisition-of-100-k9-sphs-approved|title=India's acquisition of 100 K9 SPHs approved {{!}} IHS Jane's 360|website=www.janes.com|access-date=2017-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170430150346/http://www.janes.com/article/69168/india-s-acquisition-of-100-k9-sphs-approved|archive-date=30 April 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[BM-30|Smerch 9K58 MBRL]] \n|[[File:RSZO Smertch.jpg|200x200px]]|| [[Multiple rocket launcher]] || 62 || {{RUS}} || '''Status: In service.''' 300&nbsp;mm multiple rocket la