ra]].\n|-\n| [[AT-11 Sniper|9M119 Svir <br>(AT-11 Sniper)]] \n|[[File:9M119F1 Invar-M.jpg|200px]]\n|[[Anti-tank missile|Anti-tank guided missile]] || 25000 || {{Flagu|Russia}} <br> {{Flagu|India}} || '''Status: Inducted. '''[[Bharat Dynamics]] (BDL) signed a contract with [[Ministry of Defence (India)|MOD]] for Invar anti-tank guided missiles on 19-Aug-2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pib.nic.in/newsite/erelease.aspx?relid=98429 |title=Press Information Bureau English Releases |publisher=Pib.nic.in |date= |accessdate=2013-08-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://voiceofrussia.com/2012_11_08/India-to-buy-Russia-s-Konkurs-M-Invar-guided-missiles/ |title=India to buy Russia\u2019s Konkurs-M, Invar guided missiles - News - Economy - The Voice of Russia: News, Breaking news, Politics, Economics, Business, Russia, International current events, Expert opinion, podcasts, Video |publisher=The Voice of Russia |date=2012-11-08 |accessdate=2013-08-23}}</ref> It is reported that 10000 will be procured from Russia while BDL will manufacture 15000.<ref>{{cite web|author=TNN 19 October 2012, 03.05AM IST |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-10-19/india/34583471_1_air-launched-version-brahmos-290-km-range-missile |title=Govt nod for purchase of 25,000 Invar, air-launched version of BrahMos missiles - Times Of India |publisher=Articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=2012-10-19 |accessdate=2013-08-23}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[LAHAT]]\n|[[File:LAHAT.jpg|200px]]\n|[[Cannon-launched guided projectile]]\n|\n|{{Flagu|Israel}}\n|'''Status: Inducted.''' Standard ATGM used in the main gun of Arjun Mk-1 and Mk-2 tanks.\n|-\n| [[AT-5 Spandrel|9M113 Konkurs <br>(AT-5 Spandrel)]] \n|[[File:Romanian 9P148 Konkurs cropped.jpg|200px]]|| [[Anti-tank missile|Anti-tank guided missile]] || 15,140 || {{Flagu|Russia}}<br>{{Flagu|India}} || '''Status: Inducted. '''For BMP-2 (IFV), manufactured locally in India. Total cost of the acquisition being \u20b913.77 billion.<ref>{{Cite book|url=http://www.cag.gov.in/sites/default/files/audit_report_files/Union_Government_Defence_Services_Army_Ordnance_Factories_and_Defence_PSUs_Report_19_2016.pdf|title=Report of the Comptroller and Auditor General of India, for the year ended March 2015|last=|first=|publisher=Comptroller and Auditor General of India|year=2016|isbn=|location=|pages=136}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Nag missile]] \n|[[File:Nag missile test on 8 July 2019.jpg|none|thumb|220x220px]]||[[Anti-tank missile|Anti-tank guided missile]] || 40+ (400 on order) || {{Flagu|India}} || '''Status: Inducted.''' For Namica Tank Destroyer (IFV). \n|-\n|[[Spike (ATGM)]]\n|[[File:SPIKE ATGM.jpg|200px]]\n|[[Anti-tank guided missile]]\n|210\n|{{Flagu|Israel}}\n|'''Status: Inducted.''' 210 missiles and 12 launchers at a cost of \u20b92.8 billion rupees($40.3 million).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/india/article/army-set-to-get-its-first-consignment-of-spike-anti-tank-guided-missiles-under-emergency-purchases/400825|title=Army set to get its first consignment of Spike anti-tank guided missiles under emergency purchases {{!}} India News|website=www.timesnownews.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-04-20}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Ballistic, Cruise and Anti-Ballistic Missiles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Name \n!Image\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Type \n! style=\"width:5%;\"| Numbers \n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Origin \n! Range\n|-\n| [[Brahmos]] \n|[[File:Brahmos launcher Republic day.jpg|center|frameless]]||[[Cruise missile]] ||  60-90 TELs\n|| {{Flagu|India}}<br>{{Flagu|Russia}} || '''Status: Inducted. '''300&nbsp;km range, will be updated to 600&nbsp;km range in future.\n|-\n|[[Nirbhay]] \n|[[File:Nirbhay missiles during Republic Day Parade 2018.jpg|center|frameless]]||[[Cruise missile]] ||  || {{Flagu|India}} || '''Status: Under Development/Testing(Ready By 2019-20). ''' 3 Test was held in 2016. First test was held in April/May 2016. [[Nirbhay]] with [[BrahMos (missile)|BrahMos]] seeker w