 Army, manufactured under license.\n|-\n|[[SIG Sauer P226]]<ref>https://sites.google.com/site/worldinventory/wiw_as_india</ref>\n|[[File:SIG P226 img 1624.jpg|150px]]||[[Semi-automatic pistol]]||[[9mm Parabellum|9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{GER}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by NSG.\n|-\n|[[Glock 17]]\n|[[File:Glock17.jpg|Glock 17|150px]]||[[Semi-automatic pistol]]||[[9mm Parabellum|9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{AUT}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard Special Forces pistol.\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Shotgun\n|-\n|[[Franchi SPAS-15]]\n|[[File:SPAS15.jpg|Franchi SPAS-15 Combat Shotgun|150px]]||[[Combat Shotgun]]|| 18.5 x 76&nbsp;mm NATO ||{{ITA}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces, which includes NSG.\n|-\n|[[OFB pump action Shotgun]]\n|[[File:6--sa12pagun.jpg|thumb]]\n|[[pump action]]\n|[[12-gauge shotgun]]\n|{{IND}}\n|'''Status:In Service'''\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |SMGs\n|-\n|[[Sterling submachine gun|SAF Carbine 2A1]]\n|[[File:Sterling SMG.JPG|[[SAF Carbine 2A1]]|150px]]||[[Submachine gun]]||[[9mm Parabellum|9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{IND}}<br>{{GBR}}||'''Status: In service/will be Replaced.''' [[submachine gun|SAF Carbine 1A]]. To be replaced by the [[Modern Sub Machine Carbine|MSMC]].\n|-\n|[[Uzi#Military variants|Micro-Uzi]]\n|[[File:Uzi of the israeli armed forces.jpg|Micro-Uzi|150px]]||[[Submachine gun]]||[[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{ISR}}||'''Status: In service.''' For use by Special Forces. Micro-Uzi variant used.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Army/Galleries/50-5/0548.jpg |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-11-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010190951/http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Army/Galleries/50-5/0548.jpg |archivedate=10 October 2012 |df=dmy-all }}?</ref>\n|-\n|[[Heckler & Koch MP5]]\n|[[File:Heckler & Koch MP5-1.jpg|MP5 Submachine Gun|150px]]||[[Submachine gun]]||[[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{GER}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by Indian Army Special Forces\n|-